Tall matrix 형태 데이터의 행벡터를 관측치로 사용하는 다른 언어들과 달리 줄리아에서는 wide matrix 형태 데이터의 열벡터를 관측치로 사용하는 경향이 있어, wide matrix 형태로 변환(transpose)해줘야 한다.

4.1. PCA¶

  • MultivariateStats.jl 패키지의 PCA 함수 이용
  • MultivariateStats.jl 패키지 문서: https://multivariatestatsjl.readthedocs.io/en/stable/pca.html
  • maxoutdim: 축소 차원 지정 인자
In [14]:
p = fit(PCA, data', maxoutdim = 2)
Out[14]:
PCA(indim = 6, outdim = 2, principalratio = 0.9194828785333569)
  • projection matrix 불러오기
In [15]:
P = projection(p)
Out[15]:

In general, you cannot assume that display output goes to stdout (unlike print(x) or show(x)). For example, display(x) may open up a separate window with an image. display(x) means "show x in the best way you can for the current output device(s)." If you want REPL-like text output that is guaranteed to go to stdout, use show(stdout, "text/plain", x) instead.

There are also two variants with a mime argument (a MIME type string, such as "image/png"), which attempt to display x using the requested MIME type only, throwing a MethodError if this type is not supported by either the display(s) or by x. 2. t-SNE¶

  • t-분포 확률적 임베딩
  • 줄리아에서 t-SNE를 수행하는 여러가지 방법 소개: https://github.com/nassarhuda/JuliaTutorials/blob/master/TSNE/TSNE.ipynb
  • 여기서는 싸이킷런을 이용함

3. UMAP¶

Uniform Manifold Approximation and Projection for Dimension Reduction

UMAP 문서: https://umap-learn.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html

  • UMAP의 원리는 좀 더 수학적인 이해를 필요로 하며, 추후 보완 필요
  • umap.jl GitHub: https://github.com/dillondaudert/UMAP.jl
  • 관련 블로그 포스팅: https://data.korea.ac.kr/?p=4727 / https://data-newbie.tistory.com/169
In [34]:

# my plotting function for producing visually appealing plots
function my_tsne_plot(Y, d, labels)
    colorsvec = get(ColorSchemes.tab10, labels, :extrema)
    Plots.plot(legend = false, asxis = false, grid = false)
    tsneplot = Plots.scatter!(Y[:, 1], Y[:, 2],
                        marker = (2, 2, :auto, stroke(0)), alpha = 0.8, 
                        background_color =:black,
                        color = colorsvec)
    for i = 0:9
        mx, my = mean(Y[findall(labels.==i), :], dims = 1)
        s = Shape(mx.+[-d, d, d, -d], my.+[-d, -d, d, d])
        Plots.plot!(s, 
                    color = ColorSchemes.tab10[i+1], 
                    linewidth = 0, alpha = 0.9)
        annotate!(mx, my, Plots.text(string(i), color =:white))
    end
    return tsneplot
end
